is\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6427899724895857e-33, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2453, \"end\": 2464, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"River Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"about 30 minutes\", \"from\": 2250, \"to\": 2266}, {\"ngram\": \"a three-and-a-half-hour show\", \"from\": 2272, \"to\": 2300}, {\"ngram\": \"perhaps the most drenched opening ceremony\", \"from\": 2313, \"to\": 2355}, {\"ngram\": \"the history\", \"from\": 2359, \"to\": 2370}, {\"ngram\": \"the modern Olympics\", \"from\": 2374, \"to\": 2393}, {\"ngram\": \"Hundreds of thousands\", \"from\": 2394, \"to\": 2415}, {\"ngram\": \"spectators\", \"from\": 2419, \"to\": 2429}, {\"ngram\": \"the banks\", \"from\": 2436, \"to\": 2445}, {\"ngram\": \"ponchos\", \"from\": 2474, \"to\": 2481}, {\"ngram\": \"rain jackets\", \"from\": 2486, \"to\": 2498}, {\"ngram\": \"a canopy\", \"from\": 2504, \"to\": 2512}, {\"ngram\": \"umbrellas\", \"from\": 2516, \"to\": 2525}, {\"ngram\": \"the first hint\", \"from\": 2541, \"to\": 2555}, {\"ngram\": \"raindrops\", \"from\": 2559, \"to\": 2568}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But after about an hour of the wet stuff coming down in earnest, it was clear some of the crowd had had enough.\", \"from\": 2570, \"to\": 2681, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"about an hour\", \"from\": 2580, \"to\": 2593}, {\"ngram\": \"the wet stuff\", \"from\": 2597, \"to\": 2610}, {\"ngram\": \"earnest\", \"from\": 2626, \"to\": 2633}, {\"ngram\": \"the crowd\", \"from\": 2656, \"to\": 2665}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the grandstands at the end of the Parade of Nations, exposed onlookers ran for the comfort of hospitality tents and other nearby covered areas while cameras caught the occasional thinning of the crowd along the riverside.French athletes wave flags as they sail in a boat on the river Seine during the opening ceremony for the 2024 Summer Olympics in Paris, France, Friday, July 26, 2024.Franck Fife/Pool/APThe rain was evident in the performances as dancers occasionally took tentative movements or were seen having slight slips as they performed.\", \"from\": 2682, \"to\": 3232, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3035, \"end\": 3040, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6427899724895857e-33, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 3042, \"end\": 3048, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999999999954525, \"rank\": 4.063879386080735e-12, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the grandstands\", \"from\": 2685, \"to\": 2700}, {\"ngram\": \"the end\", \"from\": 2704, \"to\": 2711}, {\"ngram\": \"the Parade\", \"from\": 2715, \"to\": 2725}, {\"ngram\": \"Nations\", \"from\": 2729, \"to\": 2736}, {\"ngram\": \"the comfort\", \"from\": 2764, \"to\": 2775}, {\"ngram\": \"hospitality tents\", \"from\": 2779, \"to\": 2796}, {\"ngram\": \"other nearby covered areas\", \"from\": 2801, \"to\": 2827}, {\"ngram\": \"cameras\", \"from\": 2834, \"to\": 2841}, {\"ngram\": \"the occasional thinning\", \"from\": 2849, \"to\": 2872}, {\"ngram\": \"the crowd\", \"from\": 2876, \"to\": 2885}, {\"ngram\": \"the riverside\", \"from\": 2892, \"to\": 2905}, {\"ngram\": \"French athletes\", \"from\": 2906, \"to\": 2921}, {\"ngram\": \"flags\", \"from\": 2927, \"to\": 2932}, {\"ngram\": \"a boat\", \"from\": 2949, \"to\": 2955}, {\"ngram\": \"the river Seine\", \"from\": 2959, \"to\": 2974}, {\"ngram\": \"the opening ceremony\", \"from\": 2982, \"to\": 3002}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2024 Summer Olympics\", \"from\": 3007, \"to\": 3031}, {\"ngram\": \"July\", \"from\": 3058, \"to\": 3062}, {\"ngram\": \"2024.Franck Fife/Pool/APThe rain\", \"from\": 3067, \"to\": 3099}, {\"ngram\": \"the performances\", \"from\": 3115, \"to\": 3131}, {\"ngram\": \"dancers\", \"from\": 3135, \"to\": 3142}, {\"ngram\": \"tentative movements\", \"from\": 3161, \"to\": 3180}, {\"ngram\": \"slight slips\", \"from\": 3201, \"to\": 3213}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The water sprung off musicians' instruments as they played and some of the boats carrying the smaller athletic delegations appeared tossed in the Seine's waves.But the Olympic spirit did not wilt in the rain.\", \"from\": 3233, \"to\": 3441, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3379, \"end\": 3384, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0042405952705265e-27, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The water\", \"from\": 3233, \"to\": 3242}, {\"ngram\": \"musicians' instruments\", \"from\": 3254, \"to\": 3276}, {\"ngram\": \"the boats\", \"from\": 3304, \"to\": 3313}, {\"ngram\": \"the smaller athletic delegations\", \"from\": 3323, \"to\": 3355}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic spirit\", \"from\": 3397, \"to\": 3415}, {\"ngram\": \"the rain\", \"from\": 3432, \"to\": 3440}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The athletes - standing in pouring rain days before they are about to compete in the most important competitions of their lives - looked beyond excited to wave to the crowds and France truly seemed to embrace the Games, though maybe most of the Parisians who did not had already left the city to flee the millions of people coming to watch the competitions.Celine Dion returns in stunning fashionThis handout released by the Olympic Broadcasting Services, shows a view of singer Celine Dion performing on the Eiffel Tower during the opening ceremony of the Paris 2024 Olympic Games Paris 2024 on July 26, 2024 in Paris, France.Handout/Screengrab by IOC/Getty ImagesAfter a stunning light show on the Eiffel Tower, one of the most iconic singers of the last several decades finally made her return to performing after four years.Celine Dionhas has been battling stiff person syndrome, a rare neurological condition that causes spasms, muscle rigidity, and a heightened sensitivity to stimuli, such as sound and lights.\", \"from\": 3442, \"to\": 4459, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3620, \"end\": 3626, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999999999954525, \"rank\": 4.063879386080735e-12, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 3867, \"end\": 3896, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Broadcasting_Services\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Olympic Broadcasting Services\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Broadcasting_Services\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Broadcasting_Services\"}, {\"begin\": 3921, \"end\": 3932, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Celine_Dion\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.66173896723299e-61, \"text\": \"Celine Dion\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Celine_Dion\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Celine_Dion\"}, {\"begin\": 4055, \"end\": 4060, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6427899724895857e-33, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The athletes\", \"from\": 3442, \"to\": 3454}, {\"ngram\": \"rain days\", \"from\": 3477, \"to\"