7234}, {\"ngram\": \"a cape\", \"from\": 7246, \"to\": 7252}, {\"ngram\": \"a-kind\", \"from\": 7265, \"to\": 7271}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The steel horse and rider gave way to the living versions of both, carrying the Olympic flag to be officially raised.A most magnificent cauldron lightingThe torchbearers French former sprinter Marie-Jose Perec and French judoka Teddy Riner arrive to light the Olympic cauldron during the opening ceremony of the Paris 2024 Olympic Games in Paris on July 26, 2024.Mohd Rasfan/AFP/Getty ImagesThe 2024 Games promised an opening ceremony unlike any other and it delivered - including on the incredible cauldron lighting.The torch was carried by scores of French athletes and other famous Olympians of now and yesteryear - including Zinedine Zidane, Rafael Nadal (who carried the torch on a boat down the Seine), Serena Williams (who rode next to Nadal), Carl Lewis and Tony Parker.And when the final torchbearers judo star Teddy Riner and 400-meter sprinter Marie-Jos\\u00e9 P\\u00e9rec lit the Olympic cauldron, which was attached to a giant balloon, it began to float.The Olympic flame ended the night hovering over the city of Paris - one last chance for the cameras to capture the incredible Parisian landscape.CNN's Sandee LaMotte contributed to this report.TagseuropefranceOlympicsParis Olympics Games 2024sports It wasn't exactly the night that Paris 2024 organizers would have hoped for (more on that in a moment).\", \"from\": 7288, \"to\": 8596, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7458, \"end\": 7464, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.995627196579294, \"rank\": 0.004362184483222859, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 7481, \"end\": 7497, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marie-Jos\\u00e9_P\\u00e9rec\", \"score\": 0.9999999999290594, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Marie-Jose Perec\", \"types\": [\"Q